I got (probably) same error, saying `video2x.json` was not found.

Maybe you need to pack `video2x.json` along with the setup file. It took me a while to realize that `video2x.json` is in source code directory.

Just in case you want log:
```
Generating Video2X configuration file
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "video2x_setup.py", line 336, in <module>
  File "video2x_setup.py", line 103, in run
  File "video2x_setup.py", line 231, in _generate_config
FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'video2x.json'
```
@deton24 Please try putting [video2x.json](https://github.com/k4yt3x/video2x/blob/master/bin/video2x.json) in the same folder with `video2x_setup.exe`. It _probably_ will fix the error.

No, it doesn't help. I have that problem too, during waifu2x-caffe installing through setup.exe the command line is closed, and in AppLocal folder there is only "ffmpeg" folder. I don't know what happens...

Has anyone got that lite version working at all?
Of course with e.g. waifu copyed.
Looks like extracting of this downloaded ffmpeg is broken.
I'll switch back to Windows tonight to see what's wrong with the setup script since so many people are having problem with it.

Try the following:

1. Open cmd.exe with Administrator privilege.
1. Navigated to the directory where video2x_setup.exe and video2x.json are stored.
1. Run `video2x_setup.exe`

If the steps above works, you should see the script finishing successfully. I would also know what's wrong if the above steps work. If the script still doesn't run successfully, at least now you'll have error messages on your screen which you can send over.

It downloads all components correctly now.

Don't know whether it was because of priviliges or runnning via CMD.

Thanks

1. V2X setup reads JSON file in its current directory, not the console's current directory.
1. V2X setup pauses and show execution summaries before exiting.
1. Print error message to request for Admin privilege on PermissionError.
